tspan.tspan: As we are now approaching the Birmingham
meeting, at the termination of which you have
fixed our match to commence, I think it would
be advisable to settle the preliminaries during
this week. Would you be good enough to state
some early period when your seconds could meet
mine, so that a contest which I have so much
at heart, and which from your eminent position
excites so much interest in the chess world,
may be looked upon as a fait accompli.
I am dear sir, yours very respectfully,
